Anyone have any idea why this condition won't evaluate to true:

```    {% set owner_id = contact.HubSpot_owner_id %}
    {% set owner_fullname = owner_id.fullname %}

    {% if owner_fullname|string == 'Kevin Donahue' %}
    &lt;tr&gt;
      &lt;td align="left" style="font-size:0px;padding:0 0px 20px;word-break:break-word;"&gt;
        &lt;div style="font-family:'Avenir Next Cyr', Helvetica, Arial, san-serif;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;line-height:25px;text-align:left;color:#47455a;"&gt;
          {{ owner_fullname }}
          dfdfdff
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
    {% else %}
    &lt;tr&gt;
      &lt;td align="left" style="font-size:0px;padding:0 0px 20px;word-break:break-word;"&gt;
        &lt;div style="font-family:'Avenir Next Cyr', Helvetica, Arial, san-serif;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;line-height:25px;text-align:left;color:#47455a;"&gt;
          Quit Genius&lt;br&gt;
          Value of owner id: {{ owner_id }}
          Value of first name: {{ owner_fullname|string }}
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt; ```
When I preview in the email I can see this printed out, and if I change the if to not equal it works, but for some reason I can't get it to evaluate to true...
